"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-football-romero-olympics-2024-tottenham-argentina-postecoglou-b1148505.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Football  Your matchday briefing on Tottenham, featuring team news and expert analysis from Sam Tabuteau    I would like to be emailed about offers, event and updates from Evening Standard. Read ourprivacy notice.  Tottenhamhead coachAnge Postecoglousays the club could blockCristian Romerofrom playing forArgentinaat theOlympicsand will \\\"strongly\\\" advise the defender to rest instead.  Romero hassaid he would \\\"love\\\" to be one of his country's three over-23 picksfor the tournament at the Paris Games, which runs from July 24 to August 10 -- finishing just a week before the start of the new Premier League season.  The Spurs vice-captain is already certain to be included in Argentina's squad for the Copa America, starting in mid-June and concluding on July 15, and Postecoglou wants Romero to be fresh for the \\\"big season\\\" ahead.  \\\"Olympics is a little bit of a different issue because club's are not obliged to let players go to the Olympics,\\\" Postecoglou said.  \\\"From that perspective, we have a little bit more of a say in it than other internationals. Certainly from our behalf as a club, we will always be looking at making sure there is a balance there.  \\\"He has not spoken to me about it, no one has spoken to me about it but I guess pretty strong advice would be with the Copa America at the same time and hopefully us gearing up for a big season next year, I'd be suggesting rest is a better policy.\\\"  Tottenham vs Luton: Prediction, kick-off time, TV, live stream, team news, h2h results, odds  Micky van de Ven offers Tottenham a major boost as defender available for Luton clash  Tottenham: No need for Ange Postecoglou panic... just look at Mikel Arteta and Jurgen Klopp examples  Tottenham'scontroversial plans for a post-season friendly against Newcastle in Melbourneon May 22, three days after the end of the campaign, have already increased the demands on their internationals ahead of the summer tournaments.  Postecoglou says he was involved in the decision to visit his hometown and insists the club carefully weighed up the pros and cons.  \\\"I guess with all these decisions there is always going to be conjecture and scrutiny around why they are made,\\\" he said.  \\\"But from our perspective, like any club, you weigh up the benefits and costs of doing something. For one reason or another, we have not had a lot of games this year and there was a unique opportunity for us to have a game at the end of the year.  \\\"I am obviously part of that discussion and we are mindful of the players and the schedule. We weighed it all up and thought it was going to be really beneficial for us as a football club, and we have gone that way.\\\"  Spurs return to action with a visit from Luton Town on Saturday and Postecoglou expects the struggling Hatters to have a go at his side, who are aiming to bounce back from achastening 3-0 defeat at Fulhambefore the international break.  \\\"You hear a lot of coaches say they are going to go all-out attack but Rob [Edwards, Luton boss] backs up his words with action,\\\" Postecoglou said.  \\\"When I have seen them play against City or Liverpool or Arsenal, any of the top clubs, they have still gone out and been really aggressive. They are going to be really aggressive against us and we have got to be ready for it.  \\\"I said after the [Fulham] game we did not work as hard as we had been in other games.  \\\"It was probably the first game this year where I felt our competitive level were not where they should have been and when they are not, you will pay a price. We did on the day and I thought Fulham were good.  \\\"We addressed it with the guys and we will have to get back up to where we have been for a tough game tomorrow.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"